AB  - The Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM), an equilibrium model for the price determination of risky assets, was developed by Sharpe [16], Lintner [9, 10] and Treynor [21], following the pioneering work of Markowitz [12, 13] and Tobin [20]. In spite of the tremendous impact of this model on the profession, the CAPM still raises many questions, and is inconsistent with a considerable body of empirical evidence.
